%description
Build a map of path-based geometry, this is a simple description of the
number of parts in an object and their basic structure. Translation and
restructuring operations for planar shapes and other hierarchical types
require a data model with a record of the underlying relationships between
elements. The gibble() function creates a geometry map, a simple record of
the underlying structure in path-based hierarchical types. There are
methods for the planar shape types in the 'sf' and 'sp' packages and for
types in the 'trip' and 'silicate' packages.

